&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-11912&quot; title=&quot;TriggerIntegrationTest fails a lot, reproducibly&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-11912&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-11912&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Improve TriggerIntegrationTest to avoid side-effects between tests (spurious autoscaling events).&lt;br/&gt;
Add a convenience method to DistribStateManager to remove data recursively.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16366856" author="jira-bot" created="Fri, 16 Feb 2018 11:14:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit d67b66b5f989ce32b24d2e6300ef5629ef98fc00 in lucene-solr&apos;s branch refs/heads/branch_7x from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ab&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ab&quot;&gt;ab&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf?p=lucene-solr.git;h=d67b66b&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf?p=lucene-solr.git;h=d67b66b&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-11912&quot; title=&quot;TriggerIntegrationTest fails a lot, reproducibly&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-11912&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-11912&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Improve TriggerIntegrationTest to avoid side-effects between tests (spurious autoscaling events).&lt;br/&gt;
Add a convenience method to DistribStateManager to remove data recursively.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16366864" author="ab" created="Fri, 16 Feb 2018 11:21:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So far as I was able to determine the most common reason for these failures were side-effects of other tests in the suite - namely, trigger configurations used in a previous test would keep generating events even after the next test was started, producing unexpected events, actions and cooldowns (waiting the cooldown period and pausing triggers that were to be tested in the current test).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;These side-effects were time-sensitive, and depended on thread contention in the JVM that executed the test suite (and other suites) - basically, stopping trigger threads took longer than the interval between finishing and starting the next test in the suite.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16366866" author="ab" created="Fri, 16 Feb 2018 11:21:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Reopen if this issue occurs again.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16370456" author="tomasflobbe" created="Tue, 20 Feb 2018 18:59:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This test keeps failing very frequently in Jenkins&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16508353" author="ab" created="Mon, 11 Jun 2018 16:48:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Resolving - I haven&apos;t seen these failures for a while now. Please reopen if it starts failing again.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
